reviews.text: This Izakaya came highly recommended by my friend so decided to try it out.  All in, a very good experience and the highlight is really the freshness of the sashimi.
Nice place, Good food, nice people
Japanese foods are always great

The standard and execution of the izakaya menu here definitely sits pretty high up on the list of Japanese restaurants to visit in Hong Kong. Tucked away at the end of an alley along Nathan Road, this nondescript eatery serves competent Japanese fare and skewers.

The only thing that stopped me from giving it a 5-star rating was the price. While quality of the food was deserving, the prices charged for each item was well above average.
Poor and embarrassing service ..you have alot to learn .. taste is just part of it..
